    label: "THE FAILURE I'M MOST HONEST ABOUT",
    body: "I skipped the discovery spike. Not accidentally — I made an active choice to skip it because I thought the architecture was strong enough that validation was a formality. I had one conversation with one PM lead and called it validated. Four months in, two of the first three product teams had already built their own solutions inside their stacks. A two-week round of structured internal interviews would have shown me that. I knew the principle. I talked myself out of applying it. That's what makes it the failure I'm most honest about.",
